olive oil
1 packet freekeh
3.5 cup water
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 Brown Onion
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
½ lime
1 cucumber
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
½ tbs honey
1 bag mint
25 packet Cow's Milk Feta
1 packet chicken breast

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Rinse the freekeh.
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Toast freekeh until fragrant, 2 minutes. Add the water and vegetable stock powder. Bring to the boil, then reduce to medium-high heat and cook until tender, 30-35 minutes.
• Drain freekeh and return to the saucepan. Cover to keep warm and set aside.

• Meanwhile, cut onion into wedges.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces, onion and chermoula spice blend on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• While the veggies are roasting, roughly chop spinach & rocket mix. Zest lime to get a pinch, then cut into wedges. Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons. Roughly chop roasted almonds. Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a small bowl, combine dill & parsley mayonnaise with a dash of water. Set aside.
• In a second small bowl, combine the honey, lime zest, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season, then mix well.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Remove from heat.

• Add roasted veggies, chicken, spinach-rocket leaves, cucumber and honey dressing to the freekeh. Stir to combine.
• Pick and thinly slice mint leaves.
• Divide pumpkin, chicken and freekeh salad between bowls.
• Top with dill-parsley dressing and crumble over feta (see ingredients).
• Garnish with almonds and mint. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!